name: Attorney General Dave Yost
tweet: Just got word that the US Supreme Court will hear oral argument on January 7 on our application for a stay of the OSHA vaccine mandate.  This isn’t about vaccines (I’m vaccinated and boosted and encourage you to talk to your doctor) This is about the limits of presidential power.

name: Attorney General Dave Yost
tweet: Ohio is leading this coalition of states challenging the OSHA vaccine mandate and we appealed to the Supreme Court of the United States early this morning.   This case will likely be a landmark decision on the limits on executive power, one way or another.  https://t.co/0QPKbEqTk0
